\f1\b  February 12, 1809.\
\

\f0\b0 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1\b On this day, Charles Robert Darwin
\f2\b0  (1809-1882) was born. He was English {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_history#Before_1900"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 naturalist}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geologist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 geologist}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biologist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 biologist}}, best known for his contributions to the science of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolution"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 evolution}}.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super  
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub His proposition that all species of life have descended over time from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_ancestors"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 common ancestors}} is now widely accepted, and considered a foundational concept in science. In a joint publication with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_Russel_Wallace"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Alfred Russel Wallace}}, he introduced his scientific theory that this {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phylogenetics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 branching pattern}} of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolution"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 evolution}} resulted from a process that he called {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_selection"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 natural selection}}, in which the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Struggle_for_existence"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 struggle for existence}} has a similar effect to the artificial selection involved in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selective_breeding"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 selective breeding}}. Darwin has been described as one of the most influential figures in human history, and he was honoured by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burials_and_memorials_in_Westminster_Abbey"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 burial in Westminster Abbey}}.\cb1 \

\f1\b \cb3 \

\f0\b0 \uc0\u55356 \u56814 \u55356 \u56825 
\f1\b \'c8 oggi l\'92anniversario della nascita di Charles Robert Darwin
\f2\b0  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/1809"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 1809}}-{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/1882"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 1882}}), {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biologia"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 biologo}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naturalista"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 naturalista}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antropologia"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 antropologo}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geologo"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 geologo}} ed {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esplorazione"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 esploratore}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regno_Unito"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 britannico}}, celebre per aver formulato la {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_dell%27evoluzione"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 teoria dell'evoluzione}} delle {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Specie"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 specie}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animali"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 animali}} e {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vegetali"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 vegetali}} per {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selezione_naturale"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 selezione naturale}} agente sulla {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Variabilit%C3%A0"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 variabilit\'e0}} dei caratteri ereditari, e della loro diversificazione e moltiplicazione per discendenza da un {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Progenitore_comune"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 antenato comune}}.
\fs24\fsmilli12370 \cb1 \

\fs28 \cb3 Pubblic\'f2 la sua teoria sull'evoluzione delle specie nel libro {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/L%27origine_delle_specie"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3\i \cf4 L'origine delle specie}}
\f3\i  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selezione_naturale"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 per selezione naturale}}
\f2\i0  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/1859"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 1859}}), che \'e8 il suo lavoro pi\'f9 noto. Raccolse molti dei dati su cui bas\'f2 la sua teoria durante un viaggio intorno al mondo sulla nave {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Beagle"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 HMS 
\f3\i Beagle}}, e in particolare durante la sua sosta alle {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gal%C3%A1pagos"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Isole Gal\'e1pagos}}.\
